  "actual_structure": "The BabyWeather Android application follows a layered feature-based modular architecture with clear separation of concerns:\n\n1. **Application Entry Point** (BabyWeatherApplication.kt) initializes the Koin DI container at process startup, managing global dependencies and configuration.\n\n2. **Activity/Navigation Layer** (MainActivity.kt + activity_main/) serves as the single-activity architecture host, managing navigation graph, bottom navigation state, and routing feature modules via NavController.\n\n3. **Feature Modules** (page_*/ directories) encapsulate user-facing features with their own ViewModels, controllers, and fragments. Each feature module has a Koin DI module (ModulesFeatureName.kt) providing its dependencies. Features include: Dashboard (weather display), Locations (location management), Settings (user preferences), Baby Settings (child profiles), Tips (weather tips), Subscription Detail (in-app purchases), Login (authentication), Location Permission (permission handling).\n\n4. **Domain Layer** (common/domain/) defines repository interfaces (LocationRepository, SettingsRepository, SubscriptionRepository) and their implementations, entity models, and DataSource abstraction for local persistence. This layer is business-logic focused and independent of Android framework specifics.\n\n5. **Infrastructure/SDK Layer** (sdk/) provides platform services: LocationManager (location and permission access), DarkModeHelper (theme management), Analytics, LoginManager, ReviewManager, and JSON serialization via Moshi. This layer bridges Android framework and third-party libraries.\n\n6. **Common/Shared Layer** (common/) provides utilities shared across features: LocalisationManager, enums (HomeType, ApplicationIcon, Page), base classes, and extension functions.\n\n7. **Resources Layer** (app/src/main/res/) defines Android resources: layout XMLs, drawables, colors, themes (with light/dark variants), animations, dimensions, strings, and navigation graph.\n\n8. **Build Configuration Layer** (build.gradle.kts, buildSrc/) centralizes dependency versions, Android SDK targets, and build variants.\n\n**Key Design Patterns**:\n- **Koin Dependency Injection**: Every feature module defines its own Koin module, composing dependencies from domain and infrastructure layers\n- **Single Activity + Navigation Graph**: All features are fragments within MainActivity, navigated via jetpack Navigation component\n- **Flow-based Reactive State**: Features use Kotlin Flows for state management (currentLocationTimeFlow, animationHelperFlow, etc.)\n- **Repository Pattern**: Abstracts data access with LocationRepository, SettingsRepository managing both local (SharedPreferences) and remote (NetworkSource) data\n- **Feature Isolation**: Features are loosely coupled, communicating via navigation events and shared domain repositories\n- **Build Variants**: Debug, Staging, and Release variants with flavor-specific resources and google-services.json\n\n**Dependency Flow**: Feature Modules → Domain Layer → Infrastructure/SDK Layer → Android Framework + Third-party Libraries"
}
